<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RZaddict</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hello friends I retired my cleric at 55 last july.. gave all hsi stuff away except no drop( full EM from hate). B/c he is human even w the no drop i only have about 138 wis. I have 1100 and 2 canes of tranquill and seb scale neck in bank.. now what i need to know is what trades can i make to boost my wis back up to around 180.. i dont know of any of the velious equippment yet. Once i get to 180 i can get back in the habit of being in good groups where we can camp better things.<P>Thanks<P>Friend</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You can sell the canes of traquility for about 750-1000pp each.<P>Then buy:<BR>2 forrest loops <BR>2 Velium jaspers rings<BR>velium ruby viel<P>total cost, 1500-2000pp<P>Additional purchases that will be cheap and easy (prices are approx):<BR>Crysoberly Talisman, 500pp<BR>Charred Guardian Shield, 200-300pp<BR>Springwood Club, 750-1000pp<BR>Adamantite Epolets, 200-300pp<P>This will put you at about 192wis.<P>For a belt, a Girdle of Diligent or a Belt of Cenobite will be fairly easy but a little more costly to come by.<P>I would also recommend you take the time to do the Aegis of Life quest (if you don't already have a cloak, it's a really good one to get. Plus it's free.)<P>If you have never been to Veliuos, then you should be at least dubious to dwarves there in thurgadin. If you have some baking skills, you can do the first 3 prayer shawl quests in an afternoon. That yeilds a range item that is ac3, 3 wis, 30mana and FREE!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>hope this helps.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Human's can't wear the belt of the cenobyte.  You might look into one of those earrings from giving rubies to that troll lady.  Name escapes me now, but it is 6ac 6wis and others, and is pretty much the best earring you can get for a human cleric.  I've heard 4-5K, but rarely sold.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aiien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ivandyr's Hoop.<P>ac 6 int 6 wis 6 hps 6 and 6 charges of some low level lifetap.<P>Give rubies to Lyunga in Innothule Swamp. She roams from near Grobb to outside Guk.<P>Take lots of rubies, like 2 stacks. Took me 27 rubies to get mine, and my enchanter friend used up 18.<P>Aiien.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Docdoertee DVine</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Works only for dark races tho, so you need a friend to do that quest for you.<P>Lifetap does 150dmg as far as I know. Used all of mine already, so I´ll have to redo that quest again. Gah.<P>And definately do the Prayer Shawl Quest for the Seal. Raising baking to 135 can be done in like 2 hours. Same for Pottery.<P>-Docdoertee</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RZaddict</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey Doc  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> u prolly dont remember me from RZ/caterva heh. Btw i already have the girdle of the diligent from fear and thanks for the other info.<P>Friend</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wamsutta</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aegis of Life quest...read up on it, put it on your back!  Also you could get a medicine totem or "small wisdom deity" for your range slot.  Head to KC or OS and get yourself a Book of Obulus for your secondary slot.  I am a human cleric, and my wisdom is over 200 (and I even wear a HORRIBLE chest piece (Jarcrap & Mithril-runed tunic depending on my ac needs for the day).<P>Wamsutta<BR>57 Templar, Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaldaea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Human might be able to do the loop quest.  It should depend on what religion you picked.  Suprisingly I was able to do the quest with a Karana Halfling druid.  I was unable to do it with an Tribunal Barbarian Shaman and a tunare wood elf druid.  I think she will give the quest to whoever is not kos with her.<P>Faction hits are with the SK guild in Oggok.  So warning to any SK friends you might have try it for you.<P>------------------<BR>Chaldaea DeBebylon - Samsara</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Catroina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually you can only equip Ivanhdrys loop if you are a race that could follow an evil good.(This was put in the game before they starting doing any deity specific stuff). But the  races that are able to use it are ones that could have someone follow and evil god. I'll check what races can actually wear it when I get on next as I wear one(human cleric). <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zygote</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>why bother starting over? AO is coming out June 27th, you can have a chance to start fresh in an entirely new game.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
